{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"33cef41e-ba62-44c6-b3af-1f1bc3a928e8","content":"No files found in the working directory — so here's exactly what to do.\n\n## 1. Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the `x:DataType` attribute pointing to your ViewModel. This opts into **compiled bindings**, which are resolved at build time instead of runtime reflection.\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" ?>\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" FontSize=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Slider Minimum=\"10\" Maximum=\"36\"\n                Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nKey change: **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** on the root element. Every `{Binding}` inside is now compiled against that type.\n\n## 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** for typos and type mismatches. To make sure they're enforced:\n\n**a) Enable warnings-as-errors (recommended):**\n\nIn your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n  <!-- or target just binding warnings: -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**b) Verify it works** — introduce a deliberate typo like `{Binding Themee}` and build. You should get a compile error, not a silent runtime failure.\n\n## 3. Scoped `x:DataType` for nested contexts\n\nIf a child element binds to a different type (e.g., inside a `CollectionView`), set `x:DataType` locally:\n\n```xml\n<CollectionView ItemsSource=\"{Binding Items}\">\n    <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>\n        <DataTemplate x:DataType=\"vm:ItemModel\">\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding Name}\" />\n        </DataTemplate>\n    </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>\n</CollectionView>\n```\n\n## Summary\n\n| What | How |\n|---|---|\n| Enable compiled bindings | Add `x:DataType` to the XAML element |\n| Catch errors at build | They're compile errors automatically; use `TreatWarningsAsErrors` to enforce |\n| Escape to classic binding | `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on a subtree |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f9d4c1dd-8f3c-4414-8d45-7d495a4bfd14","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the current directory. The user is asking a general question about how to convert a .NET MAUI page to use compiled bindings. Let me provide them with the guidance they need, including code examples.\n\nSince there are no actual files to modify, I'll explain the concept and provide example code.","outputTokens":801,"requestId":"9BDB:B0AF0:5E15D3C:694E885:69EC0E2D"},"id":"1d9c958d-2ec5-4d13-acb0-4e6e1da360d1","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:43:41.422Z","parentId":"6dd9e4d2-cdd8-488f-9ecb-997a96a2e4a8"}
